thread.title_full: Taylor Named CCSA Swimmer of the Week

title: Taylor Named CCSA Swimmer of the Week
text: 5' 11" Sr. CHARLOTTE, N.C. â€“ After aiding the Ospreys to the their first dual meet victory of the season on Saturday, senior Amy Taylor garnered Coastal Collegiate Swimming Association Swimmer of the Week honors Tuesday afternoon.Taylor won all three events she entered in the tri-meet with Campbell and North Carolina A&T on Saturday. She added two more times to the program's all-time, top-10 swims list in the meet in the 1000 freestyle and the 100 butterfly. She bested her 1000 freestyle time (10.27.84) by nearly two seconds, the seventh fastest time in school history.A week after swimming a career best in the 200 butterfly, Taylor swam her fastest time as an osprey in the 100 butterfly on Saturday. Her time of 57.14 was also the seventh fastest in school history and the fastest by any Osprey since 2012.Taylor wrapped her outstanding Saturday with a win in the 500 freestyle, turning in a time of 5:05.26. She also aided the Ospreys to their top 400 freestyle relay time of the young season, swimming the fastest 100 freestyle time of the season, turning in a split of 53.09.The swimmer of the week award is the first by an Osprey since took home the honor on Dec. 18, 2012.
